05/12/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Prosecutors pressed charges Friday (December 3rd) against Dragan Crnogorac for crimes against humanity. 
Detained last month in Banja Luka, Crnogorac, 38, is accused of taking part in the July 1995systematic execution of thousands of civilian men and boys in Srebrenica, the worst massacre in the 1992-1995 conflict. 
(Radio Free Europe, Glas Javnosti, Nezavisne Novine - 03/12/10)
